item.title: Healthy Weeknight Meals
item.dc:creator: briantumbles
item.content:encoded: Cooking can sometimes feel like a chore at the end of a busy day. It's often tempting to throw a ready meal in the oven or call for take out. But preparing a simple and healthy family meal doesn't have to be hard or time-consuming. Here are some quick wholesome dishes that you and your family will love. They can even be prepared in advance.

item.title: Better than Poutine
item.dc:creator: briantumbles
item.content:encoded: I know, what could be better that a steaming plate of fries, gravy and cheese curd? Fries, gravy, cheese curd and bacon, that's what! Throw in some fresh shallots, chilli, and a splash of roasted bone marrow and duck gravy, and we turn this popular French-Canadian dish into a something sublime.

item.title: Breakfast at my House
item.dc:creator: briantumbles
item.content:encoded: During the week we're often walking out the door with a coffee in one hand and slice of toast in the other, but on weekends breakfast is never rushed. It's a late affair, sometimes spilling over to lunch, with lots of reading and chatter in between courses of fruits, poached eggs, honey and toast. One of our favorite things we like to serve when friends are visiting are buckwheat blueberry pancakes.
